title: module 'deeplabcut' has no attribute 'pose_estimation_tensorflow'
body:
### Is there an existing issue for this?

- [X] I have searched the existing issues

### Bug description

I'm trying to get deeplabcut up and running in a tensorflow docker container, using:
-docker pull tensorflow/tensorflow  
-docker run -it tensorflow/tensorflow bash

After pip installing deeplabcut using:
- python -m pip install --upgrade pip
- pip install deeplabcut

I get the following error when importing deeplabcut:
- python
- import deeplabcut

root@aef6fcfb9ca6:/# python
Python 3.6.9 (default, Jan 26 2021, 15:33:00) 
[GCC 8.4.0] on linux

2021-09-12 09:29:16.581711: I tensorflow/stream_executor/cuda/cudart_stub.cc:29] Ignore above cudart dlerror if you do not have a GPU set up on your machine.
